reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 8, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent option if you have an Aux and USB A in close proximity.
reviews.reviewText: Used this with a vehicle that has an Aux input and a USB power in close proximity. It works way better than the adapters where you plug the charger in and an Aux cable. Those were prone to dropping out. This greatly simplify things by reducing down to one cable. I've also been using this for a little while and haven't had the drop-outs / disconnects that I had with the combo adapters that I mentioned. Very pleased with this and the construction seems very sturdy so I foresee it lasting me quite a while.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 4, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good, not great
reviews.reviewText: Good, not great. This cord works great in an older car that has an aux port but not Apple play to play music etc. The aux pigtail and lightening pigtails are an ok length, but where the cord falls short, literally and figuratively, is on the usb pigtail. In our old car the usb port is much farther away than the 6” or so that is given here. So that pigtail is basically useless. Had I realized that I would have just purchased the aux/lightening cord and not bothered with the usb portion. The cord color is great and the quality seems nice.
